        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare neurodegenerative disease characterized by progressive neurodegeneration cutaneous abnormalities including varying degrees of ichthyosis or seborrheic dermatitis and systemic iron overload. Patients manifest with infantile-onset seizures encephalopathy abnormal eye movements axial hypotonia with peripheral hypertonia brisk reflexes cortical blindness and deafness myoclonus and hepato/splenomegaly as well as oral manifestations including microdontia widely spaced and pointed teeth with delayed eruption and gingival overgrowth."
        },
